    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "What if `raw_call` were just renamed to `call`, and we made the data parameter optional (defaulting to `b\"\"`) and the gas parameter default to `2**256-1`?\r\n\r\nSo\r\n\r\n```python\r\ncall(some_address, value=some_value)\r\n```\r\n\r\nwould be the equivalent of this in Solidity:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n(bool success, ) = someAddress.call.value(someValue)(\"\");\r\nrequire(success);\r\n```",
